<div class="quotetitle">tepples wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">mikejmoffitt wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why did so many [console ports of <em>Pac-Man</em>] use this weirdly shaped maze?<br /></div><br />Because the NTSC screen is not as tall, and the console VDPs had trouble addressing areas smaller than 8x8 pixels, and I guess the various port developers thought players wouldn't prefer a scrolling maze. Or should it have been designed with 4x4 pixel tiles, with a maze only 128 pixels tall? That might have worked for the Game Boy but not elsewhere. Platforms with an all-pixels-addressable screen and without severe attribute clash of the Spectrum could have done 6x6 pixel cells and a 192 pixel maze though.</div><br /><br />Tengen got it right with Ms. Pac-Man (Tengen). Oddly, the misshapen maze in NES Pac-Man makes the center &quot;T&quot; shape where you start too tall.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5314">mikejmoffitt</a> — Wed Feb 05, 2014 8:16 am</p><hr />
