<div class="quotetitle">DRW wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br /><div class="quotetitle">lidnariq wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Why would I jest? A source code port has a better chance of being correct than one that <em>necessarily</em> requires a rewrite.<br /></div><br />Well, we don't need to speculate which version <em>could</em> be arcade-perfect. Take a look at the Spectrum version and you see that it <em>isn't</em> arcade-perfect.</div><br />It's a cost-benefit tradeoff, and everyone here has a certain amount of effort they're going to put into postings. If one had 100 ports to check and 25 of them were on Z80-based machines, it would make sense to check the Z80 ones first. It might be that one of the non-Z80 ports was best, but that's the nature of uncertainty: you make guesses based on what you know at the time.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Mon Feb 03, 2014 5:22 pm</p><hr />
